CHAT.comment: Home Visit 4; Chi and Mot sit at table , SIS1 looks over his shoulder , Chi points to letters on cover
Book Reading; The Very Hungry Caterpillar

a rather painful book reading that is over 22 minutes long; Chi is not a good reader; he often sounds out every letter; Mot uses a variety of strategies to help , including saying to sound it out , asking what sound the individual letters make , and giving the word when nothing else works; Chi seems willing to guess based on a few letters (for example Christa is read as caterpillar); Mot says at one point that Chi probably doesn't remember what was said (because of the strain of reading the words); Chi pretty much gives up when reading the second Sunday when the caterpillar eats a leaf; finally Mot reads the last few pages herself , pointing at each word; Chi comes up with words like satellite and zucchini and saddle while grasping for words
